  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "Allowlist script-src URLs with their hashes with a new keyword called url-hashes:\nSites that want to allowlist scripts for use with script-src currently have 2 options: allowlist script contents through subresource integrity, which is not practical for scripts that change often (e.g. analytics), or use host-source to allowlist entire hostnames (thus allowlisting more than may be necessary). This proposal permits allowlisting full URLs, which permits precise allowlist targeting while still allowing content to change as needed. Using hashes over raw URLs in the policy allows for a more succinct representation when allowlisting longer URLs.\n\nMore safely enabling scripts for use with eval(), Function, setTimeout, setInterval, and setImmediate:\nThe only existing mechanism to use eval() and eval-like functions is by enabling them without restriction via unsafe-eval. This means that currently any site that needs to use eval() (such as for feature detection) must expose itself to eval-based XSS risks. Allowlisting individual scripts mitigates these issues.",
  "devtrial_instructions": null,
  "activation_risks": null,
  "measurement": null,
  "availability_expectation": null,
